Taxies will not be allowed to run long hours after today. The Minister of Transport, Fikile Mbalula said the directive to allow taxies to operate the whole day was made to accommodate social grant beneficiaries. “We updated our directives to accommodate essential service works, pensioners for social grants and people in rural areas who need to access far areas for essential services,” he said in a statement. ALSO READ: TAXIS ALLOWED 70% LOADING CAPACITY! The ministry said between 30 March and 3 April 2020, buses and taxis were permitted to operate from 05:00 until 20:00. "The utilisation of sanitisation products and services, as well as the exercise of social distance by all those using public transport, must continue to be observed and enforced,” the statement read. Mbalula said taxies were only allowed to cater for 70% of their capacity and not carry full loads. As of 4 April 2020, public transport will continue operating as follows: 